/* file: index.html */ <!DOCTYPE html> <html> <head> <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css"> </head> <body> <main id="main"> <title id="title">Tim Berners-Lee</title> <h1>Tim Berners-Lee</h1> <p> The inventor of the World Wide Web.</p> <div id="img-div"><img id="image" src="https://webfoundation.org/docs/2019/03/TBL-at-Web-Summit_Letter.jpg"/><div id="img-caption">On the World Wide Web’s 30th birthday, our founder and web inventor Sir Tim Berners-Lee reflects on how the web has changed our world and what we must do to build a better web that serves all of humanity.</div></div> <section id="tribute-info"> <h2>His profile</h2> <ul> <li><span>Born:</span> 8 June 1955 (age 67 years), London, United Kingdom</li> <li><span>Awards:</span> Millennium Technology Prize, The President's Medal, MORE</li> <li><span>Spouse:</span> Rosemary Leith (m. 2014), Nancy Carlson (m. 1990–2011)</li> <li><span>Education:</span> The Queen's College (1973–1976), Emanuel School (1969–1973), Sheen Mount Primary School</li> <li><span>Children:</span> Ben Berners-Lee, Alice Berners-Lee</li> <li><span>Parents:</span> Conway Berners-Lee, Mary Lee Woods</li> </section> <h3>If you have time, you should read more about this incredible human being on his <a id="tribute-link" target="_blank" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tim_Berners-Lee"> Wikipedia entry.</a> </h3> </main> </body> </html>

